    { prompt: "What is 'Flooding' in a distillation or absorption column?", options: ["Adding too much water","A severe operational failure where the upward gas velocity is so high it prevents the liquid from flowing downward, causing liquid to rapidly accumulate and fill the column, stopping mass transfer","A leak in the pipe","Raining on the equipment"], answer: 1, difficulty: 1600, timeLimit: 20 },
    { prompt: "In pressure vessel design, what is 'Hoop Stress' (Circumferential Stress)?", options: ["Stress from playing basketball","The mechanical stress that acts tangentially to the circumference of a cylindrical vessel due to internal pressure, tending to tear the cylinder along its length (usually the largest stress to design against)","Stress on the bolts","Stress from temperature changes"], answer: 1, difficulty: 1700, timeLimit: 20 },
    { prompt: "What does the ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code (BPVC) provide?", options: ["A list of prices","The legally mandated engineering rules and safety standards governing the design, fabrication, and inspection of boilers and pressure vessels to prevent catastrophic explosions","A guide for mixing chemicals","A recipe book"], answer: 1, difficulty: 1800, timeLimit: 20 },
    { prompt: "When sizing a chemical reactor, what is 'Residence Time'?", options: ["Time spent living in the plant","The average amount of time a discrete parcel of fluid spends inside the reactor volume, critical for ensuring the chemical reaction reaches the desired conversion","The time to build the reactor","The time it takes to heat up"], answer: 1, difficulty: 1900, timeLimit: 20 }
